choices.text: being wrong.“I understand that parents should be kept under control and supported. However, they cannot kill the new lives they brought to this world,” says Khaled Saleh al-Hashmi, 28-year-old engineer from Oman.The majority of the educated youth is less likely to be in support of abortion, but is not entirely against it.“Abortion doesn’t show the mother should have been more careful. She is having a baby and it’s her first pregnancy. It happens,” says Ghazal from Oman.Few women who are in support of abortion may disagree.“The recent clashes between the protestors and the government related to embezzlement of funds are for example an example of a government not being able to develop its country the way we want to and the way we believe the money would be allocated, which can be a factor for abortion,” says Mona Rahimson, a 22-year-old working woman.Partition Global voices.
